## Proposed Changes

### Step 1 — Schema Expansion & Rules Engine

---

#### [NEW] `FocusTrack.Api/Models/AppLimit.cs`
New EF Core entity: `Id (Guid PK)`, `UserId (Guid FK → User)`, `AppName (string)`, `DailyLimitMinutes (int)`.

#### [MODIFY] `FocusTrack.Api/Data/FocusDbContext.cs`
- Add `DbSet<AppLimit> AppLimits`.
- Configure `AppLimit` entity: PK, FK to `User` (cascade delete), index on `UserId`.

#### [NEW] EF Core Migration — `AddSmartFeatures`
Run: `dotnet ef migrations add AddSmartFeatures`

#### [MODIFY] `FocusTrack.Api/Program.cs`
Switch `db.Database.EnsureCreated()` → `db.Database.Migrate()` so the new migration is applied on startup.

#### [NEW] `FocusTrack.Api/DTOs/LimitsDtos.cs`
- `SetLimitDto`: `AppName (string)`, `DailyLimitMinutes (int)` — for POST body
- `LimitAlertDto`: `AppName (string)`, `DailyLimitMinutes (int)`, `TodayUsageMinutes (int)`, `IsExceeded (bool)` — for GET response

#### [NEW] `FocusTrack.Api/Services/LimitsService.cs`
- `GetAlertsAsync(userId)`: reads user's `AppLimits`, joins today's session totals, returns `List<LimitAlertDto>`.
- `SetLimitAsync(userId, dto)`: upserts the limit for the given app name.
- `DeleteLimitAsync(userId, appName)`.

#### [NEW] `FocusTrack.Api/Controllers/LimitsController.cs`
All endpoints under `[Authorize]` and `[Route("api/limits")]`:
- `GET /api/limits/alerts` → `LimitsService.GetAlertsAsync`
- `GET /api/limits` → list of all configured limits for user
- `POST /api/limits` → `LimitsService.SetLimitAsync`
- `DELETE /api/limits/{appName}` → `LimitsService.DeleteLimitAsync`

