### Step 2 — Background Jobs & Weekly Emails (.NET)

---

#### Install Packages
```
dotnet add package Hangfire.Core
dotnet add package Hangfire.MemoryStorage
dotnet add package MailKit
```

#### [NEW] `FocusTrack.Api/Services/EmailService.cs`
- Uses `MailKit.Net.Smtp.SmtpClient` to send emails via config values in `appsettings`.
- Single method: `SendAsync(to, subject, htmlBody)`.

#### [NEW] `FocusTrack.Api/Services/WeeklyReportJob.cs`
- Pulls last 7 days of sessions for each user.
- Formats a clean HTML email with total hours focused and top 3 apps.
- Calls `EmailService.SendAsync()`.

#### [MODIFY] `FocusTrack.Api/appsettings.Development.json`
Add `Smtp` section with `Host`, `Port`, `Username`, `Password`, `From` fields (pre-filled with Ethereal placeholders).

#### [MODIFY] `FocusTrack.Api/Program.cs`
- Register `Hangfire.MemoryStorage`.
- Register `EmailService` and `WeeklyReportJob` as scoped services.
- Add `app.UseHangfireDashboard()` and `app.UseHangfireServer()`.
- Schedule recurring job: `RecurringJob.AddOrUpdate<WeeklyReportJob>("weekly-report", j => j.Execute(), Cron.Weekly)`.

